{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-markdown-js","path":"/components/ez-text-style","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Enhances text with styles to visually communicate meaning, such as emphasis.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"best-practices\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#best-practices\" aria-label=\"best practices permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Best Practices</h2>\n<p>Text style should:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be used to guide users to understand which data is important</li>\n<li>Use <code>Strong</code> to highlight important data, such as Totals in a pricing table</li>\n<li>Use <code>Subdued</code> to de-emphasize less important text, such as the second line of an address.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Text style should NOT:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be used in the place of headings. Headings break up content into sections and can be used by screen reader users to identify sections of a page the user can quickly navigate to.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<h3 id=\"text-alignment\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#text-alignment\" aria-label=\"text alignment permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Text alignment</h3>\n<p>By default, text will be left-aligned within the available space.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use <code>align</code> to control the text alignment: <code>left</code>, <code>center</code> or <code>right</code>. Alter the alignment for different screen sizes using <code>{base: 'left', medium: 'center'}</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">&#x3C;EzTextStyle align=\"center\">\n  Online ordering boosts sales through your site. ezOrdering boosts it further.\n&#x3C;/EzTextStyle>\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"strong-text-style\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#strong-text-style\" aria-label=\"strong text style permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Strong text style</h3>\n<p>Use to highlight important data, such as Totals in a pricing table.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">&#x3C;div>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;EzTextStyle use=\"strong\">Order Total&#x3C;/EzTextStyle>\n  &#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;br />\n  &#x3C;div>\n    This sentence has one &#x3C;EzTextStyle use=\"strong\">strong&#x3C;/EzTextStyle> word.\n  &#x3C;/div>\n&#x3C;/div>\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"subdued-text-style\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#subdued-text-style\" aria-label=\"subdued text style permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Subdued text style</h3>\n<p>Use to de-emphasize less important text, such as the second line of an address. Subdued text may be used to indicate empty state, for example, \"No orders placed\".</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">&#x3C;div>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;EzTextStyle use=\"subdued\">No action needed.&#x3C;/EzTextStyle>\n  &#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;br />\n  &#x3C;div>\n    This sentence has one &#x3C;EzTextStyle use=\"subdued\">subdued&#x3C;/EzTextStyle> word.\n  &#x3C;/div>\n&#x3C;/div>\n</code></pre>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Enhances text with styles to visually communicate meaning, such as emphasis."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"hr","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"best-practices","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#best-practices","aria